  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, I can confirm that **money laundering is illegal** in most jurisdictions worldwide. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) to make it appear legitimate. This process typically involves a series of transactions or activities aimed at \"cleaning\" the money so it can be used without suspicion.\n\nMost countries have laws and regulations in place to combat money laundering, and it is considered a serious criminal offense. Penalties for money laundering can include heavy fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment. Additionally, international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to set global standards and promote anti-money laundering (AML) measures.\n\nIf you have further questions or are seeking specific information about laws in a particular country, feel free to ask!",
